------------
Description:
------------
Tesseract is an OCR engine with support for unicode and the ability to recognize 
more than 100 languages out of the box. It can be trained to recognize other 
languages.
Tesseract is unable to recognize handwriting and is limited to about 64 fonts in total.

---------------------
From [PyImageSearch]:
---------------------
http://www.pyimagesearch.com/2017/07/03/installing-tesseract-for-ocr/
http://www.pyimagesearch.com/2017/07/10/using-tesseract-ocr-python/

Other:
https://www.linux.com/blog/using-tesseract-ubuntu

-------------------------
To run the tesseract OCR:
-------------------------
-> Make sure the image is:
	=> Highest resolution possible
	=> Highest contrast possible 
	=> Large as possible

$ cd to image location (if necessary)
$ tesseract image.png stdout

===============================================================================
Using Python and Tesserect:
===========================
------------
Description:
------------
Python-tesseract is a python wrapper for googleâ€™s Tesseract-OCR.

--------
Install:
--------
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo pip install pytesseract

--------
Example:
----------------------------------------------------
from pytesseract import image_to_string 
import Image
print image_to_string(Image.open('captcha.png'))
----------------------------------------------------



